      "writtenOn": "2016-08-05T00:06:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\"a particular number\" is a little vague.  How about lead with the second part, the abstract definition, something like:\n\nA fence object is considered to be signaled if all the counters of all the timelines are \u003e\u003d the corresponding target counter value for that timeline in the fence.  Timeline increments check whether the increment causes any fences to become signaled, so, signaling happens in a timely manner.\n\nJust suggesting give the abstract defn first, then the operational aspects.",
      "range": {
