        "id": 1099352
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-05T00:06:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This reads as if the reader had been told about this restriction before; I think you\u0027re introducing the restriction for the first time here.  How about something more like:\n\nAs discussed above, in general a fence can have target counter values for multiple timelines. Currently however, we only support fences with a single target counter value for a single timeline.  (etc.)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 84,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 84,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "aa8036617e4eeb4617ac056673d20ec6644d29f4",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d4762e83_e416a44b",
        "filename": "android/emulation/goldfish_sync.h",
        "patchSetId": 68
      },
      "lineNbr": 93,
      "author": {
        "id": 1099352
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-05T00:06:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In the spec for \"...create_timeline\" you gave the general definition of fence, where they can have multiple points.  Here the spec assume a single point (\"...whose point\").  I would advise writing the specs for the other methods, like this one, assuming the more general spec, while noting that the current restriction allows a simpler implementation.  So maybe: \"Any fence objects that become signaled by this increment are signaled.\"  (This sentence illustrates a tension with using signaled both for an abstract concept -- counters of referenced timelines \u003e\u003d their targets -- and a concrete one -- a signal callback gets called.  Maybe the abstract concept could become something like \"satisfied\"?  So the fence is \"satisfied\" when all the counters advance enough, and it is (concretely) signaled at some point after it becomes satisfied?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 92,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 93,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "aa8036617e4eeb4617ac056673d20ec6644d29f4",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
